        &lt;p&gt;In an appaling display of brutality, three men dragged Teresa Borrenpohl out of a town hall meeting in Coeur d&#39;Alene, Idaho. The men were repeatedly asked to identify themselves and give some indication of their authority to drag Teresa out of her seat, but refused to do so.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;Town hall attendees were angry with the representatives on stage, and several attendees were shouting out questions or criticisms when they were scolded by a disrespectful and arrogant moderator for &quot;popping off with stupid remarks.&quot; The moderator continued delivering a slew of insults aimed at the attendees, who collectively booed the moderator, but were unable to silence him. Enraged at the lack of respect these so-called representatives showed their constituents, Teresa asked, &quot;Is this a town hall, or a lecture?&quot; While the other attendees cheered Teresa&#39;s response, a local sheriff told Teresa to leave or be arrested. Meanwhile, the moderator continued delivering a non-stop deluge of insults at Teresa and the crowd in an attempt to distract the crowd&#39;s attention away from the injustice being carried out, including stating that Teresa was, a &quot;little girl,&quot; and &quot;afraid to leave.&quot; He even goes so far as to say, &quot;She spoke up, and now she doesn&#39;t want to suffer the consequences.&quot; He failed to explain why anyone should face consequences for speaking up in a town hall.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;When the sheriff was unable to talk Teresa into leaving the meeting, he called over three unidentified men wearing unmarked street clothes and then cowardly took out his cell phone, retreated to a safe distance, and started recording a video as these unidentified men grabbed Teresa and dragged her forcefully out of her chair. Teresa asked them repeatedly, &quot;who are you?&quot; They never answered the question. Teresa then turned to the sheriff and told him that she was being assaulted. Instead of coming to her aid, identifying these men, or providing any justification or official authorization for their actions, he simple continued recording, grunting, &quot;you out now,&quot; while cowering safely away from the assault taking place in front of him. She asked the sheriff if these men were his deputies, and he refused to respond or offer any indication of their identity or affiliation.&lt;/p&gt;
