&lt;h4&gt;What did I/we do?&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;table class=&quot;table table-transparent table-shadow&quot;&gt;
  &lt;tbody&gt;
    &lt;tr&gt;
    &lt;td width=&quot;200px&quot; class=&quot;caption&quot;&gt;
      &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.cbsnews.com/news/economic-blackout-feb-24-hour-february-28-2025-peoples-union/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;
        &lt;img class=&quot;img-link&quot; alt=&quot;Amazon logo with the arrow inverted to point down&quot; loading=&quot;lazy&quot; decoding=&quot;async&quot; src=&quot;/images/5V5b1A-_qD-200.webp&quot; width=&quot;200&quot; height=&quot;84&quot;&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        Feb. 28 Economic Blackout
      &lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/td&gt;
    &lt;td width=&quot;100%&quot;&gt;
      &lt;p&gt;On Friday, February 28, I joined my family and fellow patriots around the country in a one-day boycott of large corporations. I did not buy anything or visit any online or brick-and-mortar stores that day.&lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;p&gt;The impact of this boycott was probably largely unnoticed by the targeted corporations. I&#39;m sure it made a small dent in their average daily sales, but probably did nothing to actually affect their bottom lines.&lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;p&gt;But the point of this boycott was not to hurt corporate America. Instead, the point was to rally people to see if we could get a significant portion of the population to participate in an event like this. If it is possible to get enough people engaged, we might be able to enact some longer-term, more targeted boycotts that might actually have some level of impact.&lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;p&gt;For example, continuing or doubling-down on the current boycott of Target stores might pressure them into reinstating the DEI hiring policies they &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.cnn.com/2025/02/19/business/target-dei-boycott/index.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;rolled back&lt;/a&gt; out of fear that Donald Trump might &quot;investigate&quot; them. After George Floyd was murdered by police in 2020, Target became a leader in promoting DEI practices and gained a reputation as being a progressive employer. But they were also among the first companies to do an about-face in their policies as soon as Trump was elected.&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/td&gt;
    &lt;/tr&gt;
    &lt;tr&gt;
      &lt;td width=&quot;200px&quot; class=&quot;caption&quot;&gt;
        &lt;a href=&quot;/articles/fort-knox/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;
          &lt;img class=&quot;img-link&quot; alt=&quot;Painting of the U.S. Depository, Fort Knox, Kentucky&quot; loading=&quot;lazy&quot; decoding=&quot;async&quot; src=&quot;/images/_bAPEHivCt-200.webp&quot; width=&quot;200&quot; height=&quot;105&quot;&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        &lt;/a&gt;
        &lt;p class=&quot;caption&quot;&gt;&lt;a title=&quot;Tichnor Bros. Inc., Boston, Mass., Public domain, via Wikimedia Commons&quot; href=&quot;https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Gold_Vault,_U._S._Depository,_Fort_Knox,_Ky_(78762).jpg&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; class=&quot;keychainify-checked&quot;&gt;Gold Vault, U. S. Depository, Fort Knox, Ky.&lt;/a&gt; Photo from the &lt;a href=&quot;http://ark.digitalcommonwealth.org/ark:/50959/6d5706321&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; class=&quot;keychainify-checked&quot;&gt;Boston Public Library Tichnor Brothers collection #78762&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;/td&gt; 
      &lt;td&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;On Wednesday, February 26, I published the first opinion piece on this website, titled, &quot;&lt;a href=&quot;/articles/fort-knox/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Trump and  Musk to Visit Fort Knox&lt;/a&gt;.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;On February 20, Donald Trump revealed that he is planning a visit to Fort Knox to see &quot;if the gold is still there.&quot; With all of the horrible things that have happened over the past week, this is probably the least significant story, and it was quickly (and appropriately) drowned out in the torrent of disgrace pouring out of the White House every day.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;But something struck me about this statement, so I felt compelled to write this short article to document my suspicion that Trump made this statement to try to distract the press, but may have inadvertently revealed his upcoming plans to claim that someone (Probably Joe Biden or &quot;the Democrats&quot; in general) has stolen America&#39;s gold. I believe he will make this claim in an attempt to take the gold himself, or share it with Musk and/or Putin.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;It&#39;s a wild claim on my part, and probably (hopefully) is completely unjustified. But I wanted to write it down just in case it actually happens sometime soon.&lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;/td&gt;
    &lt;/tr&gt;
    &lt;tr&gt;
      &lt;td width=&quot;200px&quot; class=&quot;caption&quot;&gt;
        &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.usip.org/academy/catalog/civil-resistance-1-dynamics-nonviolent-movements&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;
          &lt;img class=&quot;img-link&quot; alt=&quot;United States Institute of Peace logo&quot; loading=&quot;lazy&quot; decoding=&quot;async&quot; src=&quot;/images/qRNyonkeSm-200.webp&quot; width=&quot;200&quot; height=&quot;58&quot;&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
          Civil Resistance Course
        &lt;/a&gt;
      &lt;/td&gt;
      &lt;td&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;This week, I signed up for the self-paced &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.usip.org/academy/catalog/civil-resistance-1-dynamics-nonviolent-movements&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;i&gt;Civil Resistance 1: The Dynamics of Nonviolent Movements&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt; course from the United States Institute of Peace.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;I&#39;m not sure how long this course will be available before Musk&#39;s rats devour the USIP along with every other government agency targeted for reduction or elimination by Donald Trump.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;But for now, I am looking forward to participating in the course. I have only completed the introduction so far, and have not yet started the true course content, which I will be participating in in the week ahead.&lt;/p&gt;
