&lt;h4&gt;What can you do in the week ahead?&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;table class=&quot;table table-transparent table-shadow&quot;&gt;
  &lt;tbody&gt;
    &lt;tr&gt;
      &lt;td width=&quot;200px&quot; class=&quot;caption&quot;&gt;
        &lt;a href=&quot;https://indivisible.org/resource/call-now-tell-your-representative-vote-no-save-act&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;
          &lt;img class=&quot;img-link&quot; alt=&quot;Indivisible Logo&quot; loading=&quot;lazy&quot; decoding=&quot;async&quot; src=&quot;/images/rlTC3hsjYJ-200.webp&quot; width=&quot;200&quot; height=&quot;200&quot;&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
          Connect to your representative
        &lt;/a&gt;
      &lt;/td&gt;
      &lt;td&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;House Republicans are pushing a bill, called the SAVE Act that intends to disenfranchise millions of eligible American voters.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;Under the guise of election security, the SAVE Act would require proof of citizenship to be presented to register to vote. When that&#39;s all you hear, it sounds very reasonable. But there are problems with this:&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;ul&gt;
          &lt;li&gt;Not everyone can access these documents (They are frequently lost or destroyed)&lt;/li&gt;
          &lt;li&gt;They must be presented in person, eliminating online and mail-in voter registration&lt;/li&gt;
          &lt;li&gt;It would prevent most married women from being able to register to vote if they changed their names when they married&lt;/li&gt;
          &lt;li&gt;It makes it easier to intimidate and add barriers to naturalized citizens&lt;/li&gt;
          &lt;li&gt;It just makes it harder in general, so fewer people will register to vote&lt;/li&gt;
        &lt;/ul&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;Indivisible has an &lt;a href=&quot;https://indivisible.org/resource/call-now-tell-your-representative-vote-no-save-act&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;online form&lt;/a&gt; you can fill out to get connected directly to your representative so you can tell them to vote NO on this dangerous bill.&lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;/td&gt;
    &lt;/tr&gt;  
    &lt;tr&gt;
      &lt;td class=&quot;caption&quot;&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://events.pol-rev.com/@50501_movement/events&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;
          &lt;img class=&quot;img-link&quot; alt=&quot;A protest rally in support of the Consumer Financial Protection Bureau and against shutting it down like president Musk and Trump are planning to do. February 10, 2025. 1275 First Street NE, Washington, DC 20002.&quot; loading=&quot;lazy&quot; decoding=&quot;async&quot; src=&quot;/images/ExEDY_LKPq-200.webp&quot; width=&quot;200&quot; height=&quot;133&quot;&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
          March 4th (forth) for Democracy
        &lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p class=&quot;caption&quot;&gt;Image by &lt;a href=&quot;https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/User:Lorax&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;G. Edward Johnson&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=&quot;https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:2025-02-10_Hands_of_the_CFPB_16-26-13.jpg&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Wikimedia Commons.&lt;/a&gt; Licensed under the &lt;a href=&quot;https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/deed.en&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Creative Commons Attribution-Share Alike 4.0 International license&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;/td&gt;
      &lt;td&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;On Tuesday, March 4th, people will gather at their state capitals or nearest cities to join the fight to uphold the Constitution and end executive overreach.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;There are many protests happening every day all across the nation. But we&#39;re pushing the &quot;March forth&quot;/&quot;March fourth&quot; protest because it is a generalized protest instead of a targeted protest (There have been protests at Tesla factories targeting Elon Musk and DOGE, protests at ICE agencies protesting immigration intimidation and racism, protests targeting women&#39;s rights, LGBTQ+ rights, Black Lives Matter, support for Ukraine, opposition to the genocide in Gaza, etc.).&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;If you&#39;d like to sign up for a protest in a city near you, you can find valuable resources along with a list of local events on the &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fiftyfifty.one&quot;&gt;50501 website&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
